The article discusses the G-8 Action on Food Security and Nutrition, which is a commitment by G-8 and African leaders to achieve global food security. The New Alliance for Food Security and Nutrition aims to increase private investments in African agriculture, promote agricultural innovations, and reduce risks for vulnerable economies and communities. The alliance recognizes the important role of smallholder farmers, especially women, in transforming agriculture and building thriving economies. The article outlines various actions and initiatives that will be taken to achieve sustained and inclusive agricultural growth, such as supporting infrastructure projects, mobilizing private capital, promoting technology adoption, managing risk, improving nutrition outcomes, and ensuring accountability for results. The New Alliance will be implemented in partnership with African organizations and will build on previous commitments made at the L'Aquila Summit.